text: Friendly atmosphere and service. Try the roti prata store, amazing for breakfast (cheese and bom). Great coffee store too with a large range of traditional coffees. Plus there is a very good soup store at Airfield, very handy for a quick dinner dabao!

Renovated, clean and open space. Variety of stalls from Noodles, Economy rice, Indian, Seafood and Western food.
Could get loud at night with regulars gathering and drinking beer.
Despite some bad reviews which concern the various other stalls, I consider the Zi Char stall pretty good. The aunty waitress is very attentive and pleasant. Food is quite nice and reasonably priced

DO NOT BUY from BOON CHIANG

Do not buy from boon Chiang chicken rice. They charge you extra and does not give you the extra that you ordered. They asked if I want to add egg, I said yes, they asked me twice, I said yes. Turns out my egg is missing. But I was charged the egg price.

Don't even know why airfield decided to let them open the stall here.

Nice coffeeshop with a big open space dining area. This coffeeshop call airfield, likely the same management team that used to managed the coffee shop next ti changi village hotel, which was called airfield.
